1
00:00:03,240 --> 00:00:04,840
Honey, why did you wear that shirt?

2
00:00:04,920 --> 00:00:06,320
You're losing it.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:09,200
What, I'm not putting in any effort for them.
-Fine, neither am I, who cares.

4
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:12,120
But like, you know, if they're filming
at least let it be respectable.

5
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:14,040
What’s with the "filming" thing, does that excite you?

6
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:17,360
Today, everywhere you go
you're caught on a thousand security cameras.

7
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:22,560
In malls, parking lots, clubs,
on Highway 6, in the fast lane.

8
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:24,360
In Ramat Gan, you're filmed, down to your bones.

9
00:00:24,440 --> 00:00:26,520
Fine, what do I care?
Let them film, what can I do?

10
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,800
Really, there's nothing to do because it won't be long

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:33,680
before everything goes live,
to YouTube, and of course, Erez Tal will host it.

12
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,280
Of course.
-And the viewers at home will vote! More

13
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:40,840
than from parking lots, from malls... Shabi Rosen,
do you have a minute to leave the mall?

14
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:44,320
Funny.
-And outside, even bigger cameras will be waiting for you.

15
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,640
If you get through this, in a month
you'll be hosting a show on Channel Two.

16
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:51,120
Fine, but aren't you a little excited?
-No, what’s that, I’m just being natural.

17
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,600
What do I care if they’re filming, or not.
-Okay.

18
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:55,560
Honey, what are you doing? There’s a camera at this intersection.

19
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,120
What, did they just film us?

20
00:00:58,920 --> 00:00:59,920
What’s up with your eyebrows?

21
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:07,080
Look at me, look at me and...

22
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:17,840
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

23
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:20,000
Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat Shalom.

24
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,800
What’s this? What did Rachel buy this time from the shopping channel?

25
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:25,360
No, it’s not Rachel, it’s not the shopping channel,

26
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,920
it’s Meirav this time.
-What’s this? Is that a karaoke machine?

27
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:31,640
Maybe
and M
Sharon

28
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:34,440
What does it matter?
-What? How’s Meirav?

29
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:38,800
Meirav, ever since she was told
she made it to the next round of "Born to Sing"

30
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:41,600
she’s been driving us crazy.

31
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:45,960
I must say, it’s a big surprise.
I didn’t even know she could sing.

32
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,640
She didn’t even know she could sing.

33
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,680
What’s this? What’s the black elephant?
-That’s it.

34
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:56,160
She wants to impress the filming crew,
like it’s just a regular thing

35
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:58,880
in our house, that we have a dishwasher,
we have a washing machine

36
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:04,560
and we also have a karaoke machine.
It gives a musical home vibe.

37
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,240
But what? But what, there’s barely a chorus.

38
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,280
For us, sol is herring.
Seriously, tell me, where’s Mom?

39
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:14,760
Right now, she’s getting a briefing from Meirav.

40
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:18,160
A briefing from Meirav. That’s interesting.

41
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,760
Because usually, you get a headache from Meirav.

42
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:27,400
Mom, you have to understand that misery
is part of every reality show competition.

43
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,720
No, that’s nonsense and I’m not up for it.

44
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,840
No, I don’t get it.
You want to direct a reality show?

45
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:38,960
The whole point of a reality show is that it’s real,

46
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:44,200
that it’s spontaneous, it’s reality.
-You cracked me up big time, Mom.

47
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,320
All this reality you see
is staged to the last detail.

48
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:50,080
People say the lines they’re given,

49
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:53,120
they make up life stories, deafness, blindness.

50
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:56,200
There’s even a rumor that the dwarf
from "Big Brother" isn’t even a dwarf.

51
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:59,240
It’s a camera trick.
-How do you know all this?

52
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:03,880
I’m telling you with certainty, Mom.
If you’re not a loser, you’re not exciting

53
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:06,560
and if you’re not exciting, you don’t get sympathy.
And if you don’t get sympathy,

54
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,560
there are no SMS votes, and if there are no SMS votes,

55
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:11,440
it means you don’t exist
even if you think you do.

56
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:15,400
You don’t want me to succeed?
-I want you to, of course, I want.

57
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,520
Good. Everything for you, it’s fine.

58
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,040
Thanks, Mom.
-Alright.

59
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:22,320
Oh, and if you could
speak a bit more with a ch and an ayin...

60
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,640
What?
-For the voices of the Mizrahim.

61
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,360
ותקראי בבקשה לאבא בדרך.

62
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,640
חית ועין?
-אימא...

63
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,840
טוב, בסדר, רק תעשי לי טובה.

64
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:38,320
כשאבא יבוא, תהיי איתו מאוד עדיבה.

65
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:42,520
שלא יחטוף התקף לב, חס וחלילה.

66
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,400
התקף לב זה מעולה,

67
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:48,560
אם זה בזמן צילומים, זה מלא אס-אם-אסים.

68
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,480
שי, אתה מבין את דף ההוראות הזה?
אני לא מסתדר עם ההיגיון הסיבוך.

69
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,840
מה, מה לא ברור, אבא?
-זה כמו סינית בשבילי.

70
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:56,880
זה בעברית.

71
00:03:57,160 --> 00:04:00,240
זה בעברית אבל זה בביב 0'ב'.
-ביב.

72
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,240
כן.
-רגע, זה לא בעיה.

73
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,680
בוא, בבקשה, תראי לי.

74
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,240
אני לוחצת כאן, להתחלה.
-בוא?

75
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:06,760
התחל. לוחצת, לוחצת.

76
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,120
פלייליסט.
-אוקיי.

77
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:10,760
ועכשיו אתה בוחר שיר,

78
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:13,920
לוחץ וזה יתחיל להתבגן.
-וואלה, כל הכבוד!

79
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:17,800
בחיי.
-רגע, חזור, חזור, חזור.

80
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:21,959
חזור, פלייליסט. קח את זה רגע.

81
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,360
איזה... הכפתורים... תראי כמה שהם קטנים,

82
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:31,360
זה כמו לסחוט קנקן של מיץ תפוזים
מתפוזים סיביים קטנים.

83
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,600
שבת שלום.
-שבת שלום.

84
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,920
שבת שלום, אימא'לה.
-שבת שלום.

85
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,880
שבת שלום. אחת, שתיים...

86
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:44,040
הנה זה עובד.
-זה הטלפון שלי.

87
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,640
מה, הרבה? כן, כן, הבחורה כבר כאן.

88
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,600
אני לא שמעתי שאסור לבוא עם פסים לטלוויזיה.

89
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,880
בן, די, אין לנו זמן. תבואו. בוא.

90
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:59,960
סאלי, מירב מחכה שתבוא לתדרוך דחוף.

91
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:03,320
מה יש לך, אימא, מה קרה לך עם החית הזאת?
-נתקע לך משהו בגרון?

92
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:08,120
אתם תגיעו למירב, אז תבינו מה אירע.

93
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,440
מה אירע?
-מה יש לה?

94
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,880
אבא יודע. אני לא צריך את התדרוכים שלה.

95
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:16,960
סאלי, היא תתעצבן.
-שתתעצבן. גם אני יודע להתעצבן.

96
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:17,920
בסדר?

97
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,360
סאלי?
-היא תתעצבן...

98
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,600
סאלי, אני מבקשת ממך. תיכנס למירב.

99
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:25,360
זה סיכוי בפלא למצוא לה חתן ראוי.

100
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,120
עוד פעם התרגיל הזה עם החתן הראוי?

101
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,480
החתן הראוי, החתן הראוי. בן, שי, בוא כבר.

102
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,760
ביום שהוא יבוא אני אציע לו שלא יבוא.

103
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:39,680
שידע כמה שאנחנו סבלנו בגללו עד שהוא בא.

104
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:45,320
החתן הראוי... או, הוא יצטער,
הוא יצטער על היום הזה שהוא בא,

105
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:49,600
החתן הראוי הזה. אדרבא,
שיבוא, שיבוא, שיראה אותן,

106
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:55,160
נראה אותו לפני שהוא הולך.
ולא חוזר. כמו כולם.

107
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,800
אבא, השלט.
-מה?

108
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,360
השלט.
-הנה השלט.

109
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:05,960
הצלחתם להתקין?
-כן. זה פשוט, זה...

110
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,760
כן
ו
זה בני

111
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:10,040
הנה. פליי.

112
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:14,160
חזור, חזור, חזור.

113
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,400
חזור, חזור.

114
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:21,320
אבא, תנסה להיות קשוב.
אני צריכה שהקהל בבית ירחם עליי.

115
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:25,280
אתה תכנס לי בול לדמות הקורבן.
-קורבן? אני?

116
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,200
כן
בני.
מה
רב.
אני כן

117
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,880
כי יש לך היסטוריה של עלבון ועליבות.

118
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:37,960
אה, וכך את תמצאי חתן?
שידע שיש לך משפחה אינפנטילית

119
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:40,000
ואבא קורבן?
-טוב, בסדר,

120
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:44,040
אתה תספר את הסיפור האישי שלי.
-כל הסיפור?

121
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:49,640
You’ll say I’m almost a widow of the IDF.
-How can you be almost a widow?

122
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:54,240
Say my almost ex-husband fell in battle.

123
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:59,120
I don’t get it. Did he fall or almost fall?
-He fell during the fight.

124
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:04,120
On a wasp's nest, and got stung by a bee,
and it turns out he was allergic,

125
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,600
so he swelled up and since then he’s been in rehab
at "Beit Levinstein."

126
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,680
Got it?
And the wasp?

127
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:14,720
Dad...
-Okay, okay, fine.

128
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,920
Fine. You’re almost a widow, he’s almost dead

129
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:22,240
and he’s almost at Beit Levinstein too.
Got it? And if they want to film,

130
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:26,120
Almost film at Beit Levinstein?
-Then we’ll say he passed away yesterday.

131
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:29,240
And if they want to film the funeral?
-Then we’ll say he’s in a coma

132
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:32,400
and he doesn’t want to be filmed.
-Because of the coma?

133
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,160
For privacy reasons.

134
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:43,280
"Rachel, look, they’ve returned to their borders..."

135
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,800
Enough, stop that.

136
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:48,000
There’s some faking going on here.
-I hope you got Dad’s singing talent

137
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,760
Meirav got from him.
-Excuse me, I’m not faking.

138
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:54,160
The one faking is this old machine.
It’s an ancient machine,

139
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:57,720
from the days when Shoshana Damari lived in a rickety shack.

140
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,440
Enough, come on, Mom, let’s go. You’re not a singer.

141
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:02,280
I remember when I was a kid
and you sang "Nomi Bumi" to me,

142
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:06,600
I closed my eyes not because I fell asleep. From the chills.

143
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:09,680
Okay, play me something else.
Here, this, this, I love this.

144
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:13,960
"Alvar, Alor, to you, Aliram."

145
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:16,440
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

146
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:19,360
Shabbat Shalom, my sweethearts. Shabbat Shalom.

147
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,400
What’s going on here?
-What is this, karaoke?

148
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:24,640
Karaoke.
-It’s with an accent. Krau-ka.

149
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:28,320
Yeah, yeah, Meirav rented this machine
to impress the filming crew,

150
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:31,600
like to show them we’re a musical and musical family.

151
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,320
Did you know the word music isn’t spelled with a "z"

152
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:36,159
but with a "t" or a pencil?

153
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:41,080
Okay, play me the song...
-No need. Come on, we heard you from downstairs.

154
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:44,480
I studied music
and 99% of people are off-key.

155
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,040
It’s not easy to sing in perfect pitch.

156
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:49,480
Yeah, it’s fine that 99 percent
are off-key in one tone, sure,

157
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:52,760
but what happens when one person is off-key among 99 good ones?

158
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,880
Funny, right?
Sure.
_Okay, who wants to

159
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,760
-Dad.

160
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:02,680
Yeah, before I forget: Shani and Shai,
to the teachers' room for a briefing with Meirav.

161
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,200
Okay, sit down, let’s finish this.

162
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:07,760
Silvan.
-Wait, who put a song for me? I want to sing.

163
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,520
What’s the problem operating this?
-Here’s the instruction sheet, put it there.

164
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:14,680
No need, just give it here. Ah, okay.
What song do you want, Dad?

165
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:18,520
This.

166
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,600
-This.

167
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:20,520
Okay.

168
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:26,320
Start, enter, choose,

169
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:29,840
go back, go back, go back.

170
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,520
I can do that too.
-Come on, give it here.

171
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:39,360
Can you act like you’re paralyzed?
-Are you normal?

172
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:44,160
Why paralyzed? Paralysis is, it’s a small creator,
it doesn’t really evoke sympathy.

173
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:47,280
Maybe we can take off a hand or a leg.
-I thought about that,

174
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:50,840
but it’s a bit hard to prove he doesn’t have a leg.
-So maybe you should bring a saw.

175
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:55,560
Sit down. I have a better idea.

176
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:58,200
Send the filming crew to film his mom.

177
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:02,400
They see Riki in action,
you get a sea of tears in the meantime.

178
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:10,080
"Alone I will go, I have no prayer.

179
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:15,360
Alone, without a future, without hope, without a dream..."

180
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:17,120
Stop.
-What happened?

181
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,440
You're off-key.

182
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:21,080
What?
-You're singing half a tone lower, as usual.

183
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:23,160
Really?
-At least it's consistent.

184
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:25,400
I can change the key.
-Go ahead, be my guest.

185
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,520
Here you go.

186
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:32,120
"I will walk alone

187
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:36,800
I have no prayer..."

188
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,880
What? What now? What now?
-I'll change it again. Okay?

189
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,200
Here you go.

190
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:50,440
"I will walk alone, I have no prayer..."

191
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:52,840
Stop.
-There's a problem.

192
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:56,520
No, the problem is with you.
-With me? Don't talk nonsense. Okay?

193
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,960
I have no problem. I've got a great voice.

194
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,160
So she got the musical side from Mom?

195
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,720
You're right, Silvan. You've got a great voice.

